{
  "stem": "1736.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First at the old address in Aken, and then our home-- the previous year this was taken, given to somebody else, and she was put into a different location, but still in Aken.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he corresponded with her for as long as she was there, which was 194-- probably beginning of '42.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- I can't tell you exactly because we have to come back to the story.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- we sort of went out to my father's side.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But now let's get back to Aken.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, what happened then was my mother was put under house arrest, meaning that she could leave the house but she couldn't travel.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She had to get special permission to travel.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then a scheme was put into place.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't exactly know the origins of it, but it was a beginning of an organization of collecting Jewish males at certain times, and Jewish children and separating families and all.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Under those situations, we were advised that I would be sent to a-- how will I describe it-- a youth hostel in Hamburg.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You want me to spell it for you?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[LAUGHING] I think anybody knows Hamburg.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that is exactly what took place.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I went to Hamburg.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in Hamburg I was put into this-- we used to call it in Hebrew [HEBREW], which means the youth house.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was also described as a [HEBREW], meaning a 'getting ready'-- I can say it in German-- but getting ready for getting ready.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[HEBREW] was really a movement where young people used to go to prepare themselves for aliyah to Israel or Palestine.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now, because we were far too young for that, [? they would ?] say this was the [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "This was a-- the-- getting prepared for being prepared.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You know, it's [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
